Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addSdpObject(25.10)                                        addSdpObject(25.10)

Name
       addSdpObject - Creates a placement blockage on top of the specified SDP
       group  OR inserts one or more empty rows across the whole die above/be-
       low the specified instance

Syntax
       addSdpObject

       [-help]

       {-obstruct  <group_name_list>  |  {-emptyRow  <instance_name>   -numRow
       <value>}}

       Creates  a  placement blockage on top of the specified SDP group OR in-
       serts one or more empty rows across the whole die above/below the spec-
       ified instance.

       Use the addSdpObject command to prevent cells from being placed  inside
       the  SDP group area. You can also use this command to create empty rows
       for clock or IPO buffers that will be inserted later on in the flow.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each addSdpObject parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man addSdpObject.

       -emptyRow <instance_name>
              Inserts empty row(s) above/below the specified instance based on
              the  justifyBy constraint of the group to which the instance be-
              longs. The empty row(s) are inserted across all SDP groups.  The
              number  of rows to be inserted is specified by the -numRow para-
              meter. If -numRow is not specified, one empty row is inserted by
              default.

              Note: The core boundary will  be  extended  to  accommodate  the
              newly added rows if the current core box is not big enough.

       -numRow <value>
              Indicates the number of empty rows to be inserted.

       -obstruct <group_name_list>
              Creates a placement blockage over the specified SDP group(s).

Examples
              * The  following  example  creates a placement blockage over the
                SDP group sdpGrp1.

                addSdpObject -obstruct sdpGrp1

              * The  following  example  inserts  two  empty  rows  below  the
                DTMF_INST/ROM_512x16_0_INST instance.

                addSdpObject -emptyRow DTMF_INST/ROM_512x16_0_INST -numRow 2

